# Clerk v7 Satellite-Domain Authentication

## **Overview**

This rule documents the **correct way** to wire a Clerk satellite domain in `@clerk/nextjs` v7+ and the **specific failure modes** that occurred during the v6 → v7 migration. The TL;DR:

- Use **URL handshake flow**, not the FAPI proxy.
- Use `clerk.redirectToSignIn()` / `redirectToSignUp()`, **never** a hand-rolled `?redirect_url=` redirect.
- Never set `*_FORCE_REDIRECT_URL` env vars to the sign-in/sign-up page URLs themselves.

If you violate any of these, the satellite SDK silently loads with `userId: null` and `__client_uat=0`, and no avatar/admin menu appears on the satellite.

---

## **Background: v6 vs v7 Satellite Behavior**

- **v6** (`@clerk/nextjs` ^6.x): satellite session establishment was **lenient** — the SDK would synthesize a session from cross-domain FAPI calls even when the return URL had no `__clerk_handshake` token. Hand-rolled `?redirect_url=` redirects happened to work *by accident*.
- **v7** (`@clerk/nextjs` ^7.0.0+): satellite session establishment is **strict** — the satellite SDK establishes a session **only** when a `__clerk_handshake=<token>` parameter is present in the return URL. Any redirect flow that doesn't generate this token leaves the satellite permanently logged out.

When upgrading from v6 → v7, audit every place that constructs a primary-domain sign-in URL by hand.

---

## **Rule 1: Use `clerk.redirectToSignIn()` / `redirectToSignUp()` on the satellite — never hand-roll the URL**

The satellite's `/sign-in` and `/sign-up` pages must detect the satellite hostname and call Clerk's redirect helpers. The helpers read `isSatellite` / `domain` / `signInUrl` from ClerkProvider and add `__clerk_satellite_url` to the primary's URL — which is what triggers Clerk to generate a `__clerk_handshake` token on the return trip.

```typescript
// ✅ DO — satellite sign-in page
'use client';
import { useClerk } from '@clerk/nextjs';

export default function SignInPage() {
  const clerk = useClerk();

  useEffect(() => {
    if (typeof window === 'undefined') return;
    const isSatellite = window.location.hostname.includes('mosc-temp.com');
    if (isSatellite) {
      // Clerk builds: https://<primary>/sign-in?__clerk_satellite_url=<satellite>&...
      // Primary returns: https://<satellite>/?__clerk_handshake=<token>&__clerk_synced=true
      clerk.redirectToSignIn({ redirectUrl: window.location.origin });
    }
  }, [clerk]);
  // ...
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T — hand-rolled redirect; bypasses Clerk's satellite logic
const signInUrl = `https://${primaryHost}/sign-in?redirect_url=${encodeURIComponent(currentUrl)}`;
window.location.href = signInUrl;
// Result on v7: primary signs the user in, redirects back to satellite as a
// plain navigation with no __clerk_handshake token. Satellite stays signed out.
```

Same pattern for sign-up — use `clerk.redirectToSignUp({ redirectUrl: window.location.origin })`.

Reference: [src/app/(auth)/sign-in/[[...sign-in]]/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/(auth)/sign-in/[[...sign-in]]/page.tsx), [src/app/(auth)/sign-up/[[...sign-up]]/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/(auth)/sign-up/[[...sign-up]]/page.tsx).

