## **Rule 3: `*_FORCE_REDIRECT_URL` env vars must NEVER point at the sign-in/sign-up page itself**

These env vars are passed as URL parameters by `clerk.redirectToSignIn()` / `redirectToSignUp()`:

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_FORCE_REDIRECT_URL` → `sign_in_force_redirect_url=` in URL
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_FORCE_REDIRECT_URL` → `sign_up_force_redirect_url=` in URL

They tell Clerk's `<SignIn>` / `<SignUp>` components: *"after a successful sign-in/up, force-redirect to this URL"*. If the URL points back at the sign-in/sign-up page, Clerk detects the loop and refuses to render the form — the page is blank.

```bash
# ❌ DON'T — points sign-in's after-redirect at sign-in itself; <SignIn /> renders blank
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_FORCE_REDIRECT_URL=https://www.event-site-manager.com/sign-in
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_FORCE_REDIRECT_URL=https://www.event-site-manager.com/sign-up
```

```bash
# ✅ DO — either remove these vars entirely (recommended) or point them at a
# post-login destination. The redirectToSignIn({ redirectUrl: window.location.origin })
# call already supplies the satellite return URL via redirect_url=…, so these
# FORCE vars are usually redundant.

# Recommended: omit them; let Clerk use defaults
# Or, if needed:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_FORCE_REDIRECT_URL=https://www.example.com/
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_FORCE_REDIRECT_URL=https://www.example.com/profile
```

Apply this to **both** primary and satellite `.env.production` files and to the corresponding AWS Amplify environment variables.

---

## **Rule 4: The satellite `ClerkProvider` config must include `isSatellite`, `domain`, and a primary `signInUrl`**

The satellite branch of `clerkProps` in `src/app/layout.tsx` must carry exactly these fields. Without `isSatellite: true`, the SDK won't trigger the satellite handshake at all.

```typescript
// ✅ DO — satellite ClerkProvider config (apply on the satellite host only)
clerkProps = isSatellite
  ? {
      isSatellite: true,
      domain: satelliteDomain,                 // e.g. 'www.mosc-temp.com'
      signInUrl: `https://${primaryDomain}/sign-in`,
      signUpUrl: `https://${primaryDomain}/sign-up`,
      afterSignOutUrl: '/',
    }
  : {
      allowedRedirectOrigins: appUrl ? [appUrl] : [],
      afterSignOutUrl: '/',
    };
```

The `domain` must match what's registered in **Clerk Dashboard → Domains → Satellites**. If you serve both bare (`example.com`) and `www.example.com`, either:

- Register **both** as satellite domains in Clerk Dashboard, **or**
- Configure a 301 redirect from bare → www at the hosting layer (Amplify/CloudFront/Route 53) so only the registered hostname ever serves traffic.

Mismatch between actual hostname and the registered satellite causes `host_invalid` on every handshake.

Reference: [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx).

